com.google.android.exoplayer

Interface TimeRange

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TimeRange.DynamicTimeRange, TimeRange.StaticTimeRange

    public interface TimeRange
    A container to store a start and end time in microseconds.

    • Nested Class Summary

      static class  TimeRange.DynamicTimeRange

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      long[] getCurrentBoundsMs(long[] out)
      Returns the start and end times (in milliseconds) of the TimeRange in the provided array, or creates a new one.
      long[] getCurrentBoundsUs(long[] out)
      Returns the start and end times (in microseconds) of the TimeRange in the provided array, or creates a new one.
      boolean isStatic()
      Whether the range is static, meaning repeated calls to getCurrentBoundsMs(long[]) or getCurrentBoundsUs(long[]) will return identical results.
